description:
Japanese title: Usagi –Sērā Mūn– (うさぎ –Sailor Moon–)

Usagi Tsukino is a bit of a clumsy and a crybaby in the 8th grade. Luna, a black cat with a crescent moon on her forehead, gives Usagi a miracle brooch.
name: Act 1 Usagi - Sailor Moon -

description:
Japanese title: Ami –Sērā Mākyurī– (亜美 –Sailor Mercury–)

Through an unexpected turn of events, Usagi becomes close with Ami Mizuno, a genius girl with an IQ of 300. But there's something odd about the students at Ami's seminar...
name: Act 2 Ami - Sailor Mercury -

description:
Japanese title: Rei –Sērā Māzu– (レイ –Sailor Mars–)

Disturbing rumors about the Sendaizakaue bus swirl all around Usagi. Amid the rumors, Usagi meets a beautiful shrine maiden with black hair named Rei Hino.
name: Act.3 Rei - Sailor Mars -

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: The Crybaby: Usagi's Beautiful Transformation.

Japanese: Nakimushi Usagi no karei naru henshin (泣き虫うさぎの華麗なる変身)

Usagi Tsukino is a 14-year-old schoolgirl who is always finding herself in unwanted trouble. One day she meets a talking cat named Luna, who reveals that dark forces are threatening the innocent. Using a magic brooch, Usagi is transforms into Sailor Moon.
name: A Moon Star Is Born

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: Punish Them! The House of Oshioki yo!

Japanese: Uranai house wa yōma no yakata, おしおきよ!占いハウスは妖魔の館

A new house of fortune opens up in the Juban District. But soon, the customers begin to act violent, including Gurio Umino, a boy who has a crush on Usagi. Suspecting that this is the work of a monster, Usagi and Luna decide to investigate.
name: Punishment Awaits: The House of Fortune Is the Monster Mansion

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: The Mysterious Sleeping Sickness: Protect the Girls in Love.

Japanese: Nazo no nemuribyō, mamore otome no koisuru kokoro (謎のねむり病, 守れ乙女の恋する心)

All the girls are tuning in to a late-night radio program called “Midnight Zero.” Meanwhile, a strange sleeping sickness plagues the town and puts many people to sleep, including Ms. Haruda and Naru.
name: Talk Radio

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: Learn How to Be Skinny from Usagi.

Japanese: Usagi ga oshiemasu! Surimu ni naruhō (うさぎが教えます!スリムになる法)

Usagi is shocked to find out that she’s gained weight from over-eating. Determined to quickly get back into shape, Usagi and her friends join a gym that advertises instant results to its members.
name: Slim City

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English:

Japanese: Yōma no kaori! Shanēra wa ai wo nusume (妖魔の香り!シャネーラは愛を盗む)

Usagi asks her family if they can keep Luna as a pet, but her little brother Shingo strongly objects out of fear. Instead, Shingo brings home a pet Chanela, a creature that smells of perfume.
name: Scent of a Monster: Chanela Will Steal Your Love

description:
Original Japanese title: Mamore koi no merodi! Usagi wa Kyūpiddo (守れ恋の曲!うさぎはキューピッド)

Usagi bumps into Yusuke Amade, a famous musician who claims he is being chased by a monster. Realizing the man is telling the truth, Usagi and Luna decide to keep an eye on Yusuke by staking out the venue where he performs.
name: Protect the Melody of Love: Usagi Plays Cupid

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: Usagi Learns Her Lesson: Becoming a Star is Hard Work.

Japanese: Usagi hansei! Sutā no michi wa kibishii (うさぎ反省!スターの道はきびしい)

Usagi and Naru both dream of becoming a famous star like Mikan Shiratori, a graduate from their school. When the girls hear that Mikan is hosting a talent contest, they see their chance to achieve stardom.
name: So You Want to Be a Superstar

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: The Girl Genius Is a Monster: The Brainwashing Cram School of Horror.

Japanese: Tensai shōjo wa yōma na no? Kyōfu no sennōjuku (天才少女は妖魔なの?恐怖の洗脳塾)

Usagi befriends Ami Mizuno, the school’s smartest girl, who has an IQ over 300. But Luna, who senses an unknown energy coming from Ami, suspects her of being a Monster.
name: Computer School Blues

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: Usagi’s Disaster: Beware of the Clock of Confusion.

Japanese: Usagi no sainan! Awate tokei ni goyōjin (うさぎの災難!あわて時計にご用心)

Usagi and Ami find a store that sells a clock resembling Luna. Later that day, Usagi’s mother gives her the same clock as a gift. But that night, the clock emits a strange light that causes Usagi to become very impatient.
name: Time Bomb

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: The Cursed Bus: Enter Mars, the Guardian of Fire.

Japanese: Norowareta basu! Honō no senshi Māzu tōjō (呪われたバス!炎の戦士マーズ登場)

Several people who take the bus near the Hikawa Shrine have started to go missing. Usagi and her friends decide to investigate by visiting the shrine, where they meet Rei Hino, a girl with strong spiritual powers.
name: An Uncharmed Life

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: Usagi vs. Rei: Nightmare in Dream Land.

Japanese: Usagi to Rei taiketsu? Yume rando no akumu (うさぎとレイ対決?夢ランドの悪夢)

The Sailor Guardians go to Dream Land amusement park, where visitors have reportedly gone missing. The team splits-up and Rei pairs with Usagi. But Usagi is more focused on playing than finding the missing people.
name: Nightmare in Dreamland

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: I Want a Boyfriend: The Luxury Cruise Ship Is a Trap.

Japanese: Watashi datte kare ga hoshii! Gōkasen no wana (私だって彼が欲しい!豪華船のワナ)

Rei goes off on a luxury cruise with Ami after winning tickets through the local lottery. Feeling left behind, Usagi sneaks aboard the ship disguised as a photographer.
name: Cruise Blues

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: Girls Unite: The End of Jadeite.

Japanese: Onna no ko wa danketsu yo! Jedaito no saigo (女の子は団結よ!ジェダイトの最期)

Jadeite is given a final warning by Queen Beryl, who can no longer tolerate the general’s continual failures. Realizing it’s his last chance, Jadeite challenges the Sailor Guardians to a showdown at the airport.
name: Fight to the Finish

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: A New Enemy Appears: Nephrite's Evil Crest.

Japanese: Arata naru kyōteki, Nefuraito ma no monshō (新たなる強敵, ネフライト魔の紋章)

Rui is a talented tennis player at Usagi’s school, but Naru has noticed a dark change in her. Worried, Naru and Usagi go to investigate at Rui’s tennis school. Meanwhile, Nephrite has stepped in to collect human energy for the great ruler.
name: Match Point for Sailor Moon

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: Usagi's Panic: Rei's First Date.

Japanese: Usagi aseru! Rei-chan hatsu dēto (うさぎアセる!レイちゃん初デート)

Ami brings Usagi and Rei to her favorite park, the perfect dating spot. Unfortunately, the place is soon to be demolished. Hearing the news, Rei decides to have a date with Mamoru at the park before it closes down, much to Usagi’s annoyance.
name: An Unnatural Phenomena

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: A Girl's Dream: Usagi Becomes a Bride.

Japanese: Junpaku doresu no yume! Usagi hanayome ni naru (純白ドレスの夢!うさぎ花嫁になる)

The Juban District is having a contest to decide who can design the best handmade wedding dress. Upon learning that the prize will be a free luxury wedding reception, Usagi, Rei, and all the girls in town compete to design their own wedding dresses.
name: Wedding Day Blues

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: Usagi's a Model: The Flash of the Monster Camera.

Japanese: Moderu wa Usagi? Yōma kamera no nessha (モデルはうさぎ?妖魔カメラの熱写)

A young photographer named Kijin Shinokawa holds a modeling contest, and Usagi decides to enter. Mysteriously, all the girls who have entered the contest begin disappearing after Shinokawa photographs them!
name: Shutter Bugged

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: Shingo's Love: The Grieving Doll.

Japanese: Shingo no junjō! Kanashimi no Furansu ningyō (進悟の純情!哀しみのフランス人形)

Shingo’s friend Mika gives him a doll she won in a doll-making contest. But Shingo unintentionally breaks it and hurts Mika’s feelings. Taking his sister Usagi’s advice, Shingo decides to apologize, only to learn that Mika does not wish to see anyone.
name: Dangerous Dollies

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: Usagi's Joy: A Love Letter from Tuxedo Mask.

Japanese: Usagi kangeki! Takishīdo Kamen no rabu retā (うさぎ感激!タキシード仮面の恋文)

Usagi receives a love letter from Tuxedo Mask, stating that he’d like to meet her. But she soon finds out that all the girls in town received the same letter, including Naru, who believes that Tuxedo Mask is Masato Sanjoin.
name: Who Is That Masked Man?

description:
Japanese title: Natsu yo Umi yo Seishun yo! Omake ni yūrei mo yo! (夏よ海よ青春よ!おまけに幽霊もよ!)

It’s summertime, and the girls search for a vacation spot so they can get away and focus on training. Instead of finding a beautiful beach destination, they settle on an ominous-looking mansion that has a very eerie service staff.
name: The Summer, the Beach, Youth and Ghosts

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: Protect the Children's Dreams: Friendship Through Anime.

Japanese: Kodomotachi no yume mamore! Anime ni musubu yūjō (子供達の夢守れ!アニメに結ぶ友情)

Ami spots Nephrite on the street and follows him down to an animation studio that is making the upcoming Sailor V movie. Suspecting that Nephrite is up to no good, Ami calls Usagi and Rei so they can investigate the studio.
name: An Animated Mess

description:
Orignal English and Japanese title:

English: Romance Under the Moon: Usagi's First Kiss.

Japanese: Gekka no romansu! Usagi no hatsu kissu (月下のロマンス!うさぎの初キッス)

The Kingdom of Diamonds is hosting a party at the embassy to reveal their royal treasure to the world. Believing that the treasure may be the Legendary Silver Crystal, both the Sailor Guardians and the Dark Kingdom crash the party to find out.
name: Worth a Princess's Ransom

description:
Orignal English and Japanese title:

English: Wish Upon a Star: Naru's First Love.

Japanese: Nagareboshi ni negai wo! Naru-chan no jun'ai (流れ星に願いを!なるちゃんの純愛)

Naru has fallen in love with Masato Sanjoin. Knowing that Sanjoin is really Nephrite, Usagi tries to convince Naru to give up on her feelings without having her learn the truth.
name: Molly's Folly

description:
Original English and Japanese title;

English: Naru's Tears: Nephrite Dies for Love.

Japanese: Naru-chan gōkyū! Nefuraito ai no shi (なるちゃん号泣!ネフライト愛の死)

Nephrite uncovers Sailor Moon’s true identity as Usagi Tsukino. But his attempt to finish her off is cut short when he learns that Naru has been kidnapped by Zoisite, who demands that Nephrite give up his Dark Crystal in exchange for the girl’s safety.
name: A Friend in Wolf's Clothing

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: Jupiter, the Powerful Girl in Love.

Japanese: Koisuru kairiki shōjo, Jupitā-chan (恋する怪力少女, ジュピターちゃん)

A new girl named Makoto Kino transfers to Usagi’s school, but her tough attitude seems to scare everyone away. Usagi, however, quickly becomes friends with her. Meanwhile, the Dark Kingdom is plotting to revive the Seven Great Monsters.
name: Jupiter Comes Thundering In

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: Restore Naru's Smile: Usagi's Friendship.

Japanese: Naru-chan ni egao wo! Usagi no yūjō (なるちゃんに笑顔を!うさぎの友情)

The Sailor Guardians grow in strength with its newest member Sailor Jupiter joining the team. Sailor Moon is appointed as team leader and is handed the Moon Stick, an item that can locate the seven Rainbow Crystals.
name: The Power of Friendship

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: Crushing on Ami: The Boy Who Can See The Future.

Japanese: Ami-chan e no koi!? Mirai yochi no shōnen (亜美ちゃんへの恋!?未来予知の少年)

Usagi learns that a transfer student named Ryo Urawa seems to have a crush on Ami, and tries to help him out. But Ryo, who secretly possesses the ability to foresee the future, finds out that he is destined to fight Ami as a Monster.
name: Mercury's Mental Match

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: The Painting of Love: Usagi and Mamoru Get Closer.

Japanese: Koi no irasuto, Usagi to Mamoru ga sekkin? (恋のイラスト, うさぎと衛が接近?)

Usagi and Naru attend an art exhibit by Yumemi Yumeno, whose works are known for helping people find love. Usagi is surprised when she and Mamoru, who also happen to be at the exhibit, are both asked by Yumemi to become models for her latest painting.
name: An Artful Attack

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: Total Chaos: The Messy Love Rectangle.

Japanese: Daikonsen! Guchagucha koi no shikaku kankei (大混戦!グチャグチャ恋の四角関係)

Usagi and Makoto are shocked to discover their crush Motoki has a girlfriend named Reika. His relationship is in jeopardy, however, due to Reika’s chance to study abroad. With nothing to lose, Usagi and Makoto aggressively go after Motoki’s affection.
name: Too Many Girlfriends

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: Grandpa Loses Control: Rei in Danger.

Japanese: Ojī-chan ranshin, Rei-chan no kiki (お爺ちゃん乱心, レイちゃんの危機)

Grandpa Hino has become emotionally unstable, causing Rei to worry. The new apprentice Yuichiro tries to cheer her up by blaming Grandpa’s behavior on the weather. Realizing that Yuichiro likes Rei, Usagi tries to help their relationship along.
name: Grandpa's Follies

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: Love and Chased: Luna's Worst Day Ever.

Japanese: Koisarete owarete! Runa no saiaku no hi (恋されて追われて!ルナの最悪の日)

Usagi and friends meet a girl who they believe holds the final Rainbow Crystal. Zoisite also pursues her. But when neither Usagi’s Moon Stick nor Zoisite’s Dark Crystal reacts to the girl, they realize it’s her pet cat that possesses the Rainbow Crystal!
name: Kitty Chaos

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: Umino's Resolve: I'll Protect Naru.

Japanese: Umino no kesshin! Naru-chan wa boku ga mamoru (海野の決心!なるちゃんは僕が守る)

Umino seems to have fallen in love with Naru. Unfortunately, Naru only considers Umino a friend, so Usagi decides to play Cupid by getting free tickets to the amusement park and urges them to go on a date together.
name: Tuxedo Melvin

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: Enter Venus, the Last Sailor Guardian.

Japanese: Saigo no Sērā Senshi, Vīnasu tōjō (最後のセーラー戦士, ヴィーナス登場)

When the exploits of a Sailor Moon imposter become quite the sensation, the real Sailor Guardians step in to investigate. They soon learn the whole thing is a trap set by the Dark Kingdom to lure out Tuxedo Mask and seize the Rainbow Crystals.
name: Sailor V Makes the Scene

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English:The Shining Silver Crystal: The Moon Princess Appears.

Japanese: Hikari kagayaku ginzuishō! Tsuki no purinsesu tōjō (光輝く銀水晶!月のプリンセス登場)

Now that Sailor V (Sailor Venus) has joined the team, all of the Sailor Guardians are finally together! Zoisite has discovered that Tuxedo Mask is actually Mamoru Chiba and challenges him to a showdown for possession of the Rainbow Crystals.
name: A Crystal Clear Destiny

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: Returning Memories: Usagi and Mamoru's Past.

Japanese: Yomigaeru kioku! Usagi to Mamoru no kako (よみがえる記憶!うさぎと衛の過去)

Tuxedo Mask is fatally wounded while protecting Sailor Moon. Responding to Sailor Moon’s tears, the seven Rainbow Crystals gather to form the Legendary Silver Crystal, and she is transformed into Serenity, the Moon Princess that everyone has been seeking.
name: A Reluctant Princess

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: Usagi's Confusion: Is Tuxedo Mask Evil?

Japanese: Usagi konran! Takishīdo Kamen wa aku? (うさぎ混乱!タキシード仮面は悪?)

Usagi is haunted by dreams of Tuxedo Mask, who has been abducted by the Dark Kingdom. Minako takes Usagi to a popular hair salon in the Juban District, hoping it will help take her friend’s mind off of her recent worries.
name: Bad Hair Day

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: Let's Become a Princess: Usagi's Bizarre Training.

Japanese: Mezase purinsesu? Usagi no chintokkun (めざせプリンセス?うさぎの珍特訓)

Usagi decides to take the Princess Seminar course at Rose Mansion to become more princess-like, and the other Sailor Guardians join her. But unbeknownst to them, this seminar is actually a trap set up by the Dark Kingdom to find Sailor Moon.
name: Little Miss Manners

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: The Snow, the Mountains, Friendship and Monsters.

Japanese: Yuki yo Yama yo Yūjō yo! Yappari yōma mo yo! (雪よ山よ友情よ!やっぱり妖魔もよ)

Usagi and friends go to a ski resort to participate in the Moon Princess Contest, unaware that it’s part of Kunzite’s plan to eliminate the real Moon Princess. During the contest, Usagi & Rei fall for the monster’s trap and get buried in the snow.
name: Ski Bunny Blues

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: Paired with a Monster: Mako, the Ice Skating Queen.

Japanese: Yōma to pea!? Hyōjō no joō Mako-chan (妖魔とペア!?氷上の女王まこちゃん)

Olympic figure-skating gold medalists Janelyn & Misha offer to coach groups of five girls. Usagi and her friends decide to investigate. Makoto, a master skater, gracefully glides across the ice and soon begins to receive personal lessons from Misha.
name: Ice Princess

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: The Legendary Lake Yokai: The Bond of Usagi's Family.

Japanese: Mizuumi no densetsu yōkai! Usagi kazoku no kizuna (湖の伝説妖怪!うさぎ家族のきずな)

Usagi goes on a family vacation to the hot springs, where she is unexpectedly reunited with Mamoru. But due to the Dark Kingdom’s brainwashing, Mamoru no longer remembers Usagi or even who he really is.
name: Last Resort

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: I Won't Run Away from Love Anymore: Ami vs. Mamoru.

Japanese: Mō koi kara nigenai! Ami to Mamoru taiketsu (もう恋から逃げない!亜美と衛対決)

The Dark Kingdom is trying again to revive the Seven Great Monsters. With five of them already under enemy control, Sailor Mercury and Jupiter scramble to protect Ryo Urawa, while Moon, Mars and Venus stay behind at Hikawa Shrine to protect Grandpa Hino.
name: Tuxedo Unmasked

description:
Japanese title: Sērā Vīnasu no kako, Minako no higeki (Sヴィーナスの過去, 美奈子の悲劇)

Minako receives a surprise visit from Katarina, an Interpol officer from the UK and Minako’s former partner while crime fighting as Sailor V. The two solved many cases together until a tragic incident forced them to go their separate ways.
name: Sailor Venus' Past, Minako's Tragic Love

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: Usagi Abandoned: The Falling-Out of the Sailor Guardians.

Japanese: Usagi ga koritsu? Sērā Senshi-tachi no ōgenka (うさぎが孤立?S戦士達の大ゲンカ)

Sailor Moon and the other Sailor Guardians appear to have a falling-out. But it’s all part of the plan to locate the enemy’s hideout. Also, a nosy journalist named Nana Asahina, who they suspect is a monster, approaches them.
name: Fractious Friends

description:
Original English and Japanese title:

English: Usagi's Awakening: A Message from the Distant Past.

Japanese: Usagi no kakusei! Chōkako no messēji (うさぎの覚醒!超過去のメッセージ)

Sailor Venus finds the Dark Kingdom's hideout. The Sailor Guardians fall into Kunzite’s trap, which hurls them into the past. The girls find themselves in a world called Silver Millennium, where they meet Queen Serenity, the mother from Usagi’s past life.
name: The Past Returns

description:
Japanese title: Sērā Senshi shisu! Hisō naru saishūsen (セーラー戦士死す!悲壮なる最終戦)

The Sailor Guardians head out into the Arctic Circle. Having anticipated their arrival, Queen Beryl sends the DD Girls, who ambush them. To Sailor Moon’s horror, the Sailor Guardians fall one after another as they try to defeat the DD Girls.
name: Death of the Sailor Guardians: The Tragic Final Battle

description:
Japanese title: Usagi no omoi wa towa ni! Atarashiki tensei (うさぎの想いは永遠に!新しき転生)

Sailor Moon confronts Queen Beryl & Endymion. She attempts to free Endymion from Queen Beryl’s control, but his brainwashing cannot be undone. With the fate of the world hanging in the balance, Sailor Moon is forced to fight the man she loves.
name: Usagi's Everlasting Wish! A New Reincarnation
